-- Morgan Creek to Buy Fund Business of Signet Capital
-- B y   C h a r l e s   S t e i n
-- 2013-05-21T13:34:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-21/morgan-creek-to-buy-fund-business-of-signet-capital.html
Morgan Creek Capital Management LLC,
a money manager that helps clients invest across asset classes
in the style of endowments, agreed to acquire the alternative-funds business of Signet Capital Management Ltd.  Signet, whose alternative-funds unit has $700 million in
assets, specializes in global fixed income and has offices in
London and Lausanne, Switzerland. The firm’s senior management
team, including founder Robert Marquardt and Chief Executive
Officer Serge Umansky, will join Morgan Creek, the Chapel Hill,
North Carolina-based manager said today in a statement.  “This agreement represents a major achievement in our
overall strategy to expand our global footprint,” Mark W. Yusko, Morgan Creek’s chief investment officer, said in the
statement.  Morgan Creek invests in a range of categories including
equities, fixed income, hedge funds, private equity, real estate
and venture capital. The transaction is expected to close in the
second quarter, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
